          "content": "Table of Contents\nIn this section, we will take a closer look at the different parts of Sherry Turkle's intriguing work. The book is organized into several key sections that guide us through her thoughts on technology and human relationships. Here’s what you can expect to find:\n- **Title Page**: This is where the book begins, introducing us to the title and author.\n- **Dedication**: Here, the author expresses gratitude to those who inspired and supported her work.\n- **Epigraph**: A thoughtful quote or saying that sets the tone for the book.\n- **Author’s Note**: In this part, Sherry shares her personal insights and intentions behind writing the book.\n- **Introduction**: This section provides an overview of the main themes and ideas that will be explored throughout the book.\n**PART ONE - The Robotic Moment**: This part dives into the fascinating world of robots and how they relate to our lives.\n**CHAPTER 1 - Nearest Neighbors**: In this chapter, we will reconsider what it means to be close to others in a world filled with technology. Topics include:\n- **Life Reconsidered**: A look at how our lives change with technology.\n- **The Tamagotchi Primer**: An introduction to the popular virtual pet and its impact on us.\n- **Unforgettable**: Stories and experiences that stick with us.\n**CHAPTER 2 - Alive Enough**: Here, we explore the question of what it means for a robot to be considered 'alive'. Key discussions include:\n- **What Does a Furby Want?**: Understanding the desires of a robotic toy.\n- **Operating Procedures**: How we interact with these machines.\n- **An Ethical Landscape**: The moral questions that arise with robotic companions.\n- **From the Romantic Reaction to the Robotic Moment**: How our feelings about technology have evolved.\n**CHAPTER 3 - True Companions**: This chapter examines the idea of companionship in the age of robots. It includes:\n- **Spare Parts**: The components that make up our robotic friends.\n- **Growing Up Aibo**: The journey of a robotic pet.\n- **From Better Than Nothing to Better Than Anything**: How our expectations of companionship have changed.\n- **Simultaneous Visions and Cold Comforts**: The mixed feelings we have about technology.\n**CHAPTER 4 - Enchantment**: In this final chapter, we look at the magical aspects of technology in our lives. Topics include:\n- **From My Real Baby to My Real Babysitter**: The shift in roles due to technology.\n- **Don’t We Have People for These Jobs?**: Questioning the need for human interaction versus robotic assistance.\nThis table of contents provides a fascinating glimpse into the discussions about technology and relationships that will unfold in the book, encouraging us to think deeply about our connections with both people and machines.\nContext recap: Table of Contents\nIn this section, we will take a closer look at the different parts of Sherry Turkle's intriguing work. The book is organized into several key sections that guide us through her thoughts on technology and human relationships. Here’s what you can expect to find:\n- **Title Page**: This is where the book begins, introducing us to the title and author. - **Dedication**: Here, the author expresses gratitude to those who inspired and supported her work.\nWhy this matters: Table of Contents ALSO BY SHERRY TURKLE Title Page Dedicatio helps learners in Technology/Psychology connect ideas from Alone Together to decisions they make during practice and assessment. Highlight tradeoffs, assumptions, and verification."
