          "id": "at-l06-c2",
          "title": "UNFORGETTABLE I took care of my first Tamagotchi at the same",
          "content": "UNFORGETTABLE: I have a vivid memory of taking care of my very first Tamagotchi, a small virtual pet that needed attention just like a real animal. At the same time, my seven-year-old daughter was also nurturing her own Tamagotchi. It was a fun experience to help her out sometimes, and in doing so, I got to observe how both of our virtual pets behaved differently. I noticed that my Tamagotchi seemed to have its own unique personality. For instance, it preferred to eat at specific times of the day and seemed to enjoy short bursts of playtime rather than long sessions. I worked hard to keep my Tamagotchi happy, making sure it was fed and played with regularly. However, I was taken aback by the sadness I felt when my Tamagotchi eventually 'died.' It was a surprising emotional moment for me, as I had not expected to feel such a strong connection to a digital pet. Without hesitation, I quickly pressed the reset button to start over with a new Tamagotchi. But to my surprise, I found that I didn't feel the same excitement about taking care of the new one that appeared on my screen. This experience made me realize that many children might not be as quick to hit the reset button. They often form real attachments to their virtual pets, showing how much they care and how these digital companions can impact their feelings. This connection highlights the importance of empathy and responsibility, even in the digital world, as we learn to nurture and care for others, whether they are real or virtual.\nContext recap: UNFORGETTABLE: I have a vivid memory of taking care of my very first Tamagotchi, a small virtual pet that needed attention just like a real animal. At the same time, my seven-year-old daughter was also nurturing her own Tamagotchi. It was a fun experience to help her out sometimes, and in doing so, I got to observe how both of our virtual pets behaved differently. I noticed that my Tamagotchi seemed to have its own unique personality.\nWhy this matters: UNFORGETTABLE I took care of my first Tamagotchi at the same helps learners in Technology/Psychology connect ideas from Alone Together to decisions they make during practice and assessment. Highlight tradeoffs, assumptions, and verification."
